# Project: cursor-guardrails

## What this is

A reusable Cursor **hub** for guardrails (rules, hooks, CI, slash commands), the playbook dashboard, and Throughline contracts — plus a minimal React + TypeScript demo so local `dev`/`typecheck`/`lint`/`test` work. **New product repos start from [cursor-guardrails-starter](https://github.com/AGM82/cursor-guardrails-starter)** (Use this template there). Existing projects adopt layers with `/guardrail-upgrade` against a reference clone of **this** hub.

## Domain glossary

- **Guardrail tier** — One layer of protection (workflow → advisory → toolchain → runtime → automation → workflows → review).
- **Deterministic enforcement** — Checks a machine runs (lint, typecheck, CI) that cannot be skipped by an AI agent.
- **Advisory rule** — Prose in `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` or `AGENTS.md`; helpful but not enforced alone.
- **Hub** — This repo (`cursor-guardrails`): playbook, AI reviews, Throughline docs, reference clone.
- **Starter** — Thin consumer template (`cursor-guardrails-starter`): Layers 1–5 + demo only.
- **templateMeta** — Hub-only paths listed in `guardrail-layers.json`; never copy into products.

## Tech stack

Default **demo** scaffold (hub + starter): React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui + Lucide React + Vitest + ESLint + Prettier + Husky. See `30-react-stack.mdc` for the three-tier stack and override process. Product repos often swap Vite for Next — record that in this file and see hub `docs/consumer-adaptations.md`.

Backend/database/deployment rules (`60`/`61`/`62`) are installed and glob-scoped so they activate when a real project adds a server, schema, or deploy step; until then they have no effect.

## Canonical files (reference these — do not reinvent)

**Child / product projects:** replace this entire section with *your* canonical paths after generate. Until you do, agents will look for the demo files below and get lost.

