- Component: `src/components/Greeting.tsx`
- Utility: `src/lib/currency.ts`
- Test: `src/components/Greeting.test.tsx`, `src/lib/currency.test.ts`
- CSS entry: `src/index.css`
- CI: `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
- Agent entry: `AGENTS.md`

## Architecture decisions

- Single-page Vite demo under `src/`; path alias `@/` → `src/`.
- Agent governance: `.cursor/rules/` (advisory), `.cursor/hooks.json` (runtime), Husky + GitHub Actions (automation).
- Branch protection on `main` requires three CI jobs before merge.
- Hub vs starter split (v1.5.0+): products generate from the starter; upgrades read this hub.

## Data classification (POPIA)

- Personal-information categories this app touches: None; templated demo data only (`formatZar` uses fake amounts).
- Retention / access constraints: N/A for templated data. Real projects must fill this section in their own `90-project-context.mdc`.

## Out of scope / do not touch

- Do not treat `src/` demo code as production features — replace when starting a real app.
- Do not commit `.env`, real client data, or credentials.
- Do not weaken CI, hooks, or security scans without explicit instruction.
